for file in df:
    qn2c= file[['DayofMonth','Month','CRSDepTime','CRSArrTime','Origin','Dest','Distance','UniqueCarrier','Diverted','CarrierDelay','WeatherDelay','NASDelay','SecurityDelay','LateAircraftDelay']].copy()

In [7]:
def categorize_distance(Distance):
    if pd.isnull(Distance):  # Handle NaN values and grouped the distance
        return 'Unknown'
    elif Distance <= 800:
        return 'Short Haul'
    elif Distance >= 2200:
        return 'Long Haul'
    else:
        return 'Medium Haul'

merged_files = []

for file in qn2c_files:
    # Merge each dataframe with 'manufacture'
    Qn2C = pd.merge(file, carriers, on="Code", how="inner")
    #Drop the column code cause what we need is the carriers name
    Qn2C.drop(columns=['Code'], inplace=True)
    Qn2C['Distance'] = Qn2C['Distance'].apply(categorize_distance)
   # Apply the function to each delay column
    Qn2C['CarrierDelay'] = Qn2C['CarrierDelay'].fillna(0).apply(lambda x: '1' if x > 0 else '0')
    Qn2C['WeatherDelay'] = Qn2C['WeatherDelay'].fillna(0).apply(lambda x: '1' if x > 0 else '0')
    Qn2C['NASDelay'] = Qn2C['NASDelay'].fillna(0).apply(lambda x: '1' if x > 0 else '0')
    Qn2C['SecurityDelay'] = Qn2C['SecurityDelay'].fillna(0).apply(lambda x: '1' if x > 0 else '0')
    Qn2C['LateAircraftDelay'] = Qn2C['LateAircraftDelay'].fillna(0).apply(lambda x: '1' if x > 0 else '0')

    Qn2C['CRSDepTime'] = pd.cut(Qn2C['CRSDepTime'], bins=[0, 600, 1200, 1800, 2400], labels=['Night', 'Morning', 'Afternoon', 'Evening'], include_lowest=True, right=False)
    Qn2C['CRSArrTime'] = pd.cut(Qn2C['CRSArrTime'], bins=[0, 600, 1200, 1800, 2400], labels=['Night', 'Morning', 'Afternoon', 'Evening'], include_lowest=True, right=False)
    Qn2C['CarrierDelay']=Qn2C["CarrierDelay"]
    
    merged_files.append(Qn2C)
    print(Qn2C)

# Loop through each DataFrame in Qn2C_list
for df in merged_files:
    
    # Apply one-hot encoding to 'CRSDepTime', 'CRSArrTime', and 'Distance' columns also avoids dummy variable trap
    X_encoded = pd.get_dummies(df[['CRSDepTime', 'CRSArrTime', 'Distance','Carriers']], drop_first=True)
    
    top_10_carriers=df["Carriers"].value_counts().nlargest(10).index
    Qn2C_top_10= df[df["Carriers"].isin(top_10_carriers)]
    
    # Split data into train and test sets
    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X_encoded, df['Diverted'], test_size=0.2, random_state=42)
    

    # Scale features
    scaler = StandardScaler()
    X_train_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train)
    X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test)
    

    # Fit logistic regression model
    model = LogisticRegression()
    model.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train)

    # Get coefficients
    coefficients = model.coef_[0]

    # Visualize coefficients
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.bar(X_encoded.columns, coefficients)
    plt.xlabel('Feature')
    plt.ylabel('Coefficient')
    plt.title('Logistic Regression Coefficients')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
